clean the slate and start over.

38:51.086 --> 38:53.167
Why?

38:55.799 --> 38:57.909
Did you tell him?

38:58.009 --> 39:00.505
- You tell him.
- Tell me what?

39:01.930 --> 39:04.916
The two of you are gonna be bigger
than Burns and Allen.

39:05.016 --> 39:09.600
Bigger than Hope and Crosby.
Bigger than all of 'em.

39:16.152 --> 39:21.391
I got all these advisors. Who's the guy that
goes out and gets the laughs every night?

39:21.491 --> 39:24.060
It's you, Eddie. You are the one.

39:24.160 --> 39:26.980
And that's why
I'm gonna go bring her over.

39:27.080 --> 39:29.941
I wish you wouldn't do that.

39:30.041 --> 39:32.122
Want some aspirin?

39:38.299 --> 39:41.202
- Come on.
- No, I don't think so.

39:41.302 --> 39:45.832
He feels terrible about what happened.
He just needs you to break the ice.

39:45.932 --> 39:48.084
- Go on, Dixie.
- Go ahead.

39:48.184 --> 39:50.680
He's disconsolate. Come on.

39:54.524 --> 39:57.844
What would I have to give you
for one little kiss?

39:57.944 --> 40:00.025
Chloroform.

40:03.700 --> 40:06.955
Eddie, you remember Dixie Leonard.

40:07.787 --> 40:10.330
Yeah, I remember. So...

40:10.832 --> 40:12.913
So...

40:13.835 --> 40:16.129
You have something to say?

40:17.589 --> 40:21.757
Yeah. I don't like
the way you talk to my uncle.

40:22.886 --> 40:24.955
What is your problem, lady?

40:25.055 --> 40:29.209
My problem, Eddie,
is you can't walk all over people.

40:29.309 --> 40:31.670
It makes a bad impression.

40:31.770 --> 40:36.383
- I guess that's what's held me back.
- That's what's held you back as a person.

40:36.483 --> 40:39.427
Oh, God. Right through the heart.

40:39.527 --> 40:41.608
I mean, if I had one.

40:42.489 --> 40:46.184
That's enough. Sit down,
have a drink, for Christ's sakes.

40:46.284 --> 40:49.646
No, I'm gonna get some sleep.
I'm sorry it didn't work out.

40:49.746 --> 40:51.827
Dixie.

40:55.669 --> 40:59.339
I give up. What do I have to do?

41:01.341 --> 41:04.347
You could try saying you're sorry.

41:14.354 --> 41:17.276
Apologise. Go fix it.

41:24.155 --> 41:25.820
Let us pray.

41:26.616 --> 41:31.563
- Two-bit Napoleon. I bet you he wears lifts.
- You can't take him personally.

41:31.663 --> 41:35.831
- Him and Hitler have the same agent.
- Good line.

41:37.794 --> 41:41.133
- He's just like all the rest of them.
- Give us a song, Eddie.

42:41.066 --> 42:43.147
I apologise.

42:45.445 --> 42:50.326
- Just relax and follow my lead.
- Yeah, right off a cliff.

43:00.085 --> 43:02.571
You just let me teach you
and nothing'll stop us.

43:02.671 --> 43:08.243
We'll be bigger than Burns and Allen,
bigger than Hope and Crosby.

43:08.343 --> 43:11.265
We'll be bigger than all of them.

43:13.640 --> 43:15.684
OK.

43:21.147 --> 43:24.134
- Oh, my God. What's that?
- It's an air raid.

43:24.234 --> 43:28.555
- What do we do?
- Do? Nothing can happen to you.

43:28.655 --> 43:30.949
You're with Eddie Sparks.

43:43.420 --> 43:45.989
And he was right,

43:46.089 --> 43:50.388
You could feel it, He was invincible,

43:51.720 --> 43:55.999
Nothing could happen to you
if you were with Eddie Sparks.

43:56.099 --> 43:58.180
He just had magic.

44:00.311 --> 44:03.899
And how they loved him, those boys.

44:05.900 --> 44:08.511
Airfields,

44:08.611 --> 44:10.692
camps,

44:11.823 --> 44:13.287
hospitals.

44:14.242 --> 44:16.121
He was something.

44:17.620 --> 44:19.701
Generous...

44:20.332 --> 44:22.413
stingy...

44:24.002 --> 44:25.631
infuriating...

44:27.130 --> 44:29.211
brilliant.

44:31.384 --> 44:35.932
A world-class,
solid-gold son of a bitch.

44:44.314 --> 44:46.758
Liked the ladies, did he?

44:46.858 --> 44:51.471
He screwed everything that moved,
between Portsmouth and Yokohama.

44:51.571 --> 44:52.607
