- It's not important what I want.

01:04:47.892 --> 01:04:52.464
Eddie wants you to pull yourself together.
It's renewal time, Dixie.

01:04:52.564 --> 01:04:58.678
Come on. You're gonna go out there
and you're gonna do the sketch like a pro.

01:04:58.778 --> 01:05:01.986
And strictly from the script, right?

01:05:08.288 --> 01:05:10.899
- That son of ours is something.
- What happened?

01:05:10.999 --> 01:05:14.569
I'm tucking him in bed last night.
He says "Is kissing dirty?"

01:05:14.669 --> 01:05:16.905
- What'd you tell him?
- I said to him:

01:05:17.005 --> 01:05:20.617
"Sex between two people
can be a beautiful thing."

01:05:20.717 --> 01:05:23.343
"But between four people, fantastic!"

01:05:24.804 --> 01:05:26.517
Oh, come on.

01:05:28.224 --> 01:05:32.726
Everybody clear.
Get the music started. Here we go.

01:05:34.314 --> 01:05:37.092
Well, that's our show.
We hope you liked it.

01:05:37.192 --> 01:05:41.096
We sure liked doing it for you.
And until next week, remember...

01:06:19.275 --> 01:06:21.950
We're two minutes short.
Give them a fill.

01:06:46.886 --> 01:06:48.967
Too short?

01:06:49.973 --> 01:06:54.169
Time, we're short time.
Two minutes time.

01:06:54.269 --> 01:06:57.005
Do you have any ideas
what we can do in two minutes?

01:06:57.105 --> 01:06:59.316
Not unless you're part-rabbit.

01:07:06.573 --> 01:07:09.935
The truth is I have been
thinking of something.

01:07:10.035 --> 01:07:12.395
This'll be a surprise to you too, Dix.

01:07:12.495 --> 01:07:16.858
There's a war happening
halfway across the world

01:07:16.958 --> 01:07:20.415
in a lonely place called Korea,

01:07:20.920 --> 01:07:28.954
So, I was thinking maybe you, me, Wally and
the boys, we give 'em a little Christmas cheer

01:07:29.054 --> 01:07:31.831
and do our Christmas show
in the Yokohama harbour.

01:07:31.931 --> 01:07:34.427
Applause. Push the button.

01:07:40.357 --> 01:07:42.438
What do you say?

01:07:47.072 --> 01:07:50.976
Well, Eddie, as long as
we're talking about helping the boys,

01:07:51.076 --> 01:07:54.771
now would be a good time to share
with everyone the magnificent gesture

01:07:54.871 --> 01:07:56.940
that this man made today.

01:07:57.040 --> 01:07:59.818
There's a time for speaking out
and a time to be modest.

01:07:59.918 --> 01:08:04.281
I know that all your fans will be delighted
to know that earlier today

01:08:04.381 --> 01:08:11.580
Eddie made a personal contribution
to the International Red Cross of $100,000.

01:08:11.680 --> 01:08:14.935
What a guy!

01:08:17.268 --> 01:08:19.349
That's my bonus.

01:08:22.232 --> 01:08:24.395
We're out of time, folks.

01:08:37.913 --> 01:08:40.955
Me! Me!

01:08:45.212 --> 01:08:47.294
You.

01:09:08.278 --> 01:09:11.096
Tune in next week
and join our special guests:

01:09:11.197 --> 01:09:16.102
Bobo, the wonder chimp, Vicky LaRue
and Chester, and the Flying Feldmans.

01:09:16.202 --> 01:09:19.956
For Bailey's coffee,
I'm Niles LaGuardia.

01:09:26.171 --> 01:09:29.991
- You couldn't say $50,000?
- You're lucky I didn't say a million.

01:09:30.091 --> 01:09:35.455
All right, so... maybe I shouldn't have
sprung it on you like that.

01:09:35.555 --> 01:09:39.042
- I just thought it'd be more dramatic.
- It was dramatic all right.

01:09:39.142 --> 01:09:43.096
- Only trouble is I ain't going.
- Yes, you are.

01:09:45.273 --> 01:09:47.567
- Korea.
- And Japan.

01:09:48.609 --> 01:09:51.345
- Get outta here. I gotta get dressed.
- Mom?

01:09:51.446 --> 01:09:54.265
- Yes, son?
- I'm with Mrs Sparks and the girls.

01:09:54.366 --> 01:09:56.659
We'll be right there. Dix.

01:09:57.827 --> 01:09:59.908
Look...

01:10:02.082 --> 01:10:06.987
- You know what they got in Japan?
- Yeah, radiation.

01:10:07.087 --> 01:10:10.240
That's funny. That's not all.

01:10:10.340 --> 01:10:14.327
It's... I can't tell you.
It's a fabulous, fabulous country.

01:10:14.427 --> 01:10:19.937
There's mountains and hotels...
Come on outta there, will you?

01:10:20.392 --> 01:10:24.254
They got all these rituals.
They got these special tubs.

01:10:24.354 --> 01:10:29.259
You get in... two people...
and they rub the soap round you.

01:10:29.359 --> 01:10:33.430
- What's Margaret gonna do? Hold the towel?
- What is the matter with you?

01:10:33.530 --> 01:10:38.852
Soon it's gonna be too late. You'll say "Me
and Eddie could've been beautiful together."

01:10:38.952 --> 01:10:41.730
It really works
when you talk to people like this?

01:10:41.830 --> 01:10:45.859
- You tell me you don't want it.
- I don't want it.

01:10:45.959 --> 01:10:48.904
- You're lying.
- It's not a sex problem with you.

01:10:49.004 --> 01:10:51.085
It's a hearing problem.

01:10:53.425 --> 01:10:58.163
- Hi, Mom. You were great.
- The show was wonderful. I loved it.

01:10:58.263 --> 01:11:00.344
Hi, Uncle Eddie.

01:11:02.809 --> 01:11:04.878
- You guys really going to Korea?
- Yeah.

01:11:04.978 --> 01:11:10.425
But you're all going to join us in Japan for
Christmas. Won't that be wonderful, Eddie?

01:11:10.525 --> 01:11:15.263
- Oh, Eddie. What a lovely idea.
- Keep the families together.

01:11:15.363 --> 01:11:19.059
That's so important
in these uncertain times, don't you think?

01:11:19.159 --> 01:11:23.355
So tell me about this Korea place.
What's it like?

01:11:23.455 --> 01:11:26.579
You're gonna love it.
It's a tropical paradise.

01:11:43.099 --> 01:11:46.294
Just like the Polo Lounge.
Give you something to write about.

01:11:46.394 --> 01:11:49.422
I've never endured
such discomfort before in my life.

01:11:49.522 --> 01:11:54.302
- War is hell. You can quote me on that.
- Go away, go away.

01:11:54.402 --> 01:11:56.483
Get outta the way!

01:11:57.405 --> 01:12:00.826
Get outta here! Get outta here! Come on!

01:12:02.327 --> 01:12:04.646
Goddammit. Lousy gooks.

01:12:04.746 --> 01:12:08.191
What do you expect?
These people have no character.

01:12:08.291 --> 01:12:10.527
They got no shoes, lady.

01:12:10.627 --> 01:12:13.863
That's irrelevant.
It's a matter of national character.

01:12:13.963 --> 01:12:16.950
Excellent point, Luanna.
Include it in your next column.

01:12:17.050 --> 01:12:20.245
- They're freezing. Can't we do anything?
- We are.

01:12:20.345 --> 01:12:24.124
We're saving them from Communism.
See their happy faces?

01:12:24.224 --> 01:12:28.044
Cos they don't have to sleep
under some oppressive Communist blanket.

01:12:28.144 --> 01:12:34.009
What would you suggest, Mr Silver? We stand
aside and let the Communists take over?

01:12:34.109 --> 01:12:37.637
No. I think we should teach
the Communists our military strategy,

01:12:37.737 --> 01:12:39.931
then they'll be sure to lose.

01:12:40.031 --> 01:12:43.393
- Is that a joke?
- Lady, this whole war's a joke.

01:12:43.493 --> 01:12:46.618
- And you can quote me on that.
- Come here.

01:12:51.876 --> 01:12:57.032
- Are you nuts? Are you nuts?
- Eddie, she's a gossip columnist.

01:12:57.132 --> 01:13:02.078
In 200 newspaper outlets, a friend of J Edgar
Hoover's, every network head in her pocket,

01:13:02.178 --> 01:13:04.706
and you wanna trade quips with her?

01:13:04.806 --> 01:13:08.293
She'll bury you!
And I don't want you taking me with you.

01:13:08.393 --> 01:13:10.337
Forget it.

01:13:10.437 --> 01:13:13.423
She is doing a major story on me. Major.

01:13:13.523 --> 01:13:16.426
I don't care what you think about
on your own time,

01:13:16.526 --> 01:13:21.193
but when you're on salary,
you button it up, all right?

01:13:24.242 --> 01:13:29.272
- Fucking war. Gets everybody crazy.
- Let's load up the trucks right now!

01:13:29.372 --> 01:13:31.441
- We're getting outta here.
- What's up?

01:13:31.541 --> 01:13:35.153
Chinks just jumped in with both feet.
They overran the base an hour ago.

01:13:35.253 --> 01:13:36.752
- Our base?
- Not any more.

01:13:46.139 --> 01:13:49.167
- What the hell's this?
- Do you believe this?

01:13:49.267 --> 01:13:50.627
- Damn.
- Stop!

01:13:50.727 --> 01:13:53.046
- We got trouble, Eddie.
- What's going on?

01:13:53.146 --> 01:13:55.590
- Stop!
- Hold it. What's that?

01:13:55.690 --> 01:13:58.260
- Stop the truck!
- It's a trap.

01:13:58.360 --> 01:14:02.138
- It's a marine.
- We got wounded.

01:14:02.238 --> 01:14:05.392
- We got VIPs here, man.
- I got fucking wounded!

01:14:05.492 --> 01:14:07.894
- What's the problem?
- There's been an ambush.

01:14:07.994 --> 01:14:12.732
There's men all over the place.
I gotta get these trucks down there.

01:14:12.832 --> 01:14:15.328
- Move!
- Let's go. Hold on.

01:14:34.187 --> 01:14:38.439
You're gonna be fine.
You're on your way home now.

01:14:42.320 --> 01:14:45.575
You OK, kid? You're going home.

01:14:55.166 --> 01:14:58.820
I need another pair of hands here!
I need some help, goddammit!

01:14:58.920 --> 01:15:03.116
Hang in there, fella. Hold this.
Over here.

01:15:03.216 --> 01:15:05.297
Here. Hold it steady.

01:15:07.095 --> 01:15:12.542
Put pressure here. Let it loose every 15
minutes for 30 seconds or he'll lose a leg.

01:15:12.642 --> 01:15:18.006
I need stretcher bearers!
Hold this tight. Who the hell are you?

01:15:18.106 --> 01:15:20.816
- Dixie Leonard.
- The singer?

01:15:22.902 --> 01:15:25.221
Crazy goddamn war.

01:15:25.321 --> 01:15:28.099
Hang in there, fella. Hang in there.

01:15:28.199 --> 01:15:31.061
30 seconds every 15 minutes,
Dixie Leonard.

01:15:31.161 --> 01:15:33.039
Let's go! Let's move it out!

01:15:43.089 --> 01:15:47.702
- It's bad, isn't it?
- They're gonna fix you right up.

01:15:47.802 --> 01:15:49.883
- Swear to God.
- Sure.

01:15:51.014 --> 01:15:53.854
Me and Humpty Dumpty.

01:16:00.899 --> 01:16:03.385
Holy shit.

01:16:03.485 --> 01:16:05.387
Eddie Sparks.

01:16:05.487 --> 01:16:09.406
- It's OK. You don't gotta get up.
- Yeah. Right.

01:16:21.211 --> 01:16:23.292
Where you from?

01:16:24.255 --> 01:16:25.838
Wilkes-Barre.

01:16:28.301 --> 01:16:30.180
I played Wilkes-Barre.

01:16:51.574 --> 01:16:54.728
You're gonna be fine.
You're on your way home now.

01:16:54.828 --> 01:16:56.909
Careful, careful.

01:16:57.664 --> 01:16:59.745
I gotta go with him.

01:17:01.459 --> 01:17:03.540
His leg.

01:17:04.671 --> 01:17:07.532
- Hold it. Down.
- The tourniquet. He told me...

01:17:07.632 --> 01:17:10.660
- I know, ma'am. I got it.
- Careful!

01:17:10.760 --> 01:17:14.164
The medic said his leg would be OK.

01:17:14.264 --> 01:17:17.186
Pupils fixed and dilated. He's dead.

01:17:18.476 --> 01:17:21.087
- Belly wound. He never had a chance.
- He can't be.

01:17:21.187 --> 01:17:24.049
- Miss, please.
- No, but he said...

01:17:24.149 --> 01:17:28.317
No, but... But he can't be!
He can't be dead!

01:17:39.080 --> 01:17:41.244
Excuse me, Miss Leonard.

01:17:43.001 --> 01:17:45.070
Follow me, please.

01:17:45.170 --> 01:17:47.251
Please, Miss Leonard.

01:17:49.049 --> 01:17:51.130
Let's go, Mr Sparks.

01:18:05.690 --> 01:18:11.221
This is yours, Mr Sparks. Miss Leonard,
you're the last one on the left, OK?

01:18:11.321 --> 01:18:13.402
Thank you.

01:18:16.868 --> 01:18:18.949
Just kids.

01:18:19.829 --> 01:18:22.207
That's some fucking thing.

01:18:23.291 --> 01:18:26.214
Just a kid. About 19 or 20.

01:18:30.382 --> 01:18:32.463
Sh.

01:18:34.886 --> 01:18:37.872
- Stay with me, Dix.
- Oh, Eddie.

01:18:37.972 --> 01:18:40.765
No, not like that. I...

01:18:42.686 --> 01:18:44.767
I just...

01:18:45.397 --> 01:18:47.924
I don't know.

01:18:48.024 --> 01:18:50.947
I don't wanna be alone, OK?

01:19:12.757 --> 01:19:15.051
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:19:16.845 --> 01:19:18.926
You're up early.

01:19:19.973 --> 01:19:22.054
Always.

01:19:24.728 --> 01:19:26.809
So what do you think?

01:19:32.152 --> 01:19:34.220
You know what I think?

01:19:34.320 --> 01:19:41.289
What I think is this Luanna is gonna get up
any minute, sticking her nose around.

01:19:44.414 --> 01:19:48.251
She'd like this one, too, Luanna.
You and me.

01:19:50.398 --> 01:19:52.443
She'd print it too.

01:19:54.110 --> 01:19:56.191
Jesus.

01:19:57.071 --> 01:19:59.152
Margaret'd kill me.

01:20:12.503 --> 01:20:15.213
- What's wrong?
- Nothing.

01:20:17.592 --> 01:20:22.306
A bunch of guys got killed and we got laid.
Am I missing something?

01:20:26.434 --> 01:20:29.191
- Sorry you feel like that.
- You'll get over it.

01:20:36.277 --> 01:20:42.350
Dixie, last night
was really very, very special.

01:20:42.450 --> 01:20:45.812
Yeah. And we'll always have Paris.

01:20:45.912 --> 01:20:48.606
I swear, I don't know
how to talk to you sometimes.

01:20:48.706 --> 01:20:54.216
Eddie, it's really OK.
But you oughta quit while you're behind.

01:21:15.692 --> 01:21:17.773
Tamaki Kawakubo!

01:21:21.030 --> 01:21:22.577
Domo arigato,

01:21:28.538 --> 01:21:30.619
I'd like to make a toast.

01:21:35.169 --> 01:21:40.700
Eddie, Dixie, on behalf of our fighting
men and women everywhere,

01:21:40.800 --> 01:21:43.343
you're doing a magnificent job.

01:21:44.095 --> 01:21:49.770
To you, to your troupe,
we love you and God bless you.

01:21:50.226 --> 01:21:52.003
- Hip, hip!
- Hooray!

01:21:52.103 --> 01:21:53.129
- Hip, hip!
- Hooray!

01:21:53.229 --> 01:21:55.026
- Hip, hip!
- Hooray!

01:21:57.025 --> 01:22:00.031
- Nice party.
- Yeah, I've had worse.

01:22:04.073 --> 01:22:10.146
Eddie, the sponsors are getting
a lot of heat about this writer of yours.

01:22:10.246 --> 01:22:14.109
- Art Silver.
- Art Silver? What kind of heat?

01:22:14.209 --> 01:22:18.460
Well, they... they say he's a Red.

01:22:19.505 --> 01:22:23.159
He signed some things.
I don't know what.

01:22:23.259 --> 01:22:26.371
He's not gonna overthrow anything.
He's a comedy writer.

01:22:26.471 --> 01:22:32.877
I know that, but these guys have got a bug
up their ass about this whole commie thing.

01:22:32.977 --> 01:22:36.631
Yeah, well, I'll talk to him.

01:22:36.731 --> 01:22:40.271
Yeah, well, it's past that.

01:22:41.236 --> 01:22:43.732
They want him off the show.

01:22:44.405 --> 01:22:48.184
- That's ridiculous.
- Eddie, they're ready to walk.

01:22:48.284 --> 01:22:51.855
I mean it. They're not signing
unless he's off the payroll.

01:22:51.955 --> 01:22:55.442
- They want you to handle it now.
- What do you mean, now?

01:22:55.542 --> 01:22:57.986
- Tonight.
- It's Christmas.

01:22:58.086 --> 01:23:02.407
Eddie, we are talking
about a five-year renewal.

01:23:02.507 --> 01:23:05.003
Now, please, think about it.

01:23:08.596 --> 01:23:12.041
I'll tell you what, fuck doing the work.
Go to another network.

01:23:12.141 --> 01:23:16.546
They're all the same. They're all
cleaning house. Actors, directors, writers.

01:23:16.646 --> 01:23:18.965
It's a bloodbath.

01:23:19.065 --> 01:23:23.649
Eddie, my friend,
that's just the way things are now.

01:23:26.781 --> 01:23:30.727
Me and Art...
18 years we've been together.

01:23:30.827 --> 01:23:34.773
You gotta stop thinking about just yourself.
You got a lot of responsibility.

01:23:34.873 --> 01:23:41.295
You got a lot of people on the payroll.
You can't afford to be controversial.

01:23:58.563 --> 01:24:02.400
Is this a private party
or can anybody get in?

01:24:23.379 --> 01:24:26.385
And have you been a good little boy?

01:24:27.008 --> 01:24:29.077
Listen, you got a minute?

01:24:29.177 --> 01:24:31.720
All right, smile!

01:24:32.263 --> 01:24:34.344
Good, that's terrific.

01:24:37.602 --> 01:24:42.269
- Nice to have you aboard.
- Thank you. Nice being here.

01:24:44.234 --> 01:24:46.315
It's done.

01:24:48.655 --> 01:24:52.527
Merry Christmas!

01:24:59.958 --> 01:25:04.654
Oh, my heavens.
Is that Miss Luanna Trott?

01:25:04.754 --> 01:25:08.045
What do we have for little Luanna today?

01:25:10.260 --> 01:25:12.787
Something to get around on.

01:25:12.887 --> 01:25:14.581
Ho-ho-ho!

01:25:14.681 --> 01:25:17.889
- I'll save it for Halloween.
- Good sport, Luanna.

01:25:19.269 --> 01:25:20.795
Ho-ho-ho!

01:25:22.313 --> 01:25:24.757
And who have we here?
What's your name, son?

01:25:24.857 --> 01:25:29.512
- Come on, Uncle Art. It's me, Danny.
- Danny, you rotten little kid.

01:25:29.612 --> 01:25:34.017
What you got on your hat there, Danny?
I see some writing on your hat.

01:25:34.117 --> 01:25:36.269
USS Missouri.

01:25:36.369 --> 01:25:42.662
And here it is. A perfect replica
of the USS Missouri for you.

01:25:46.754 --> 01:25:50.543
Oh, and Mr Admiral.
We haven't forgotten you.

01:25:51.509 --> 01:25:56.915
Mr Admiral has big responsibilities
during the Christmas period.

01:25:57.015 --> 01:26:00.001
What could we give to Mr Admiral?

01:26:00.101 --> 01:26:02.003
Oh, my goodness.

01:26:02.103 --> 01:26:08.718
Another replica of his ship,
the USS Missouri.

01:26:08.818 --> 01:26:12.806
- She never looked better.
- And no shelling the civilians, promise?

01:26:12.906 --> 01:26:14.987
I promise.

01:26:16.326 --> 01:26:21.231
And who's this lovely lady?
I'll bet you we have something really nice.

01:26:21.331 --> 01:26:26.027
Well, let's see here. It's an autographed
picture of her husband,

01:26:26.127 --> 01:26:31.968
personally inscribed: "To Margaret.
Best wishes. Eddie Sparks."

01:26:34.761 --> 01:26:37.257
I'll cherish this for ever.

01:26:39.807 --> 01:26:42.377
God, it isn't. Is it?

01:26:42.477 --> 01:26:45.672
I don't have my glasses.
It is. It's Eddie Sparks.

01:26:45.772 --> 01:26:50.176
- Have you been a good boy, Eddie?
- Don't do this.

01:26:50.276 --> 01:26:53.199
Don't do this? This is what I do.

01:26:54.530 --> 01:26:59.185
Don't be a schmuck.
We'll work it out under the table, all right?

01:26:59.285 --> 01:27:06.752
Under the table? I can't work under
the table. That's where all the rats are.

01:27:07.544 --> 01:27:12.839
And now, boys and girls,
it's time for Uncle Eddie's present!

01:27:14.008 --> 01:27:16.255
Ho-ho-ho-ho-ho!

01:27:29.023 --> 01:27:32.528
Oh, look, Eddie. There's a note.

01:27:33.861 --> 01:27:37.816
- Why don't you read it?
- Why don't you read it?

01:27:39.951 --> 01:27:42.032
OK, I will.

01:27:51.629 --> 01:27:53.710
"Dear Eddie."

01:27:57.176 --> 01:28:00.266
"I wrote my first joke
for you on this, June 1932."

01:28:04.100 --> 01:28:08.254
"I thought you should have it...
for your trophy case."

01:28:08.354 --> 01:28:11.111
Signed: "Your pal."

01:28:14.861 --> 01:28:16.942
"Art."

01:28:22.243 --> 01:28:27.607
Well, boys and girls,
it's time to go back to the North Pole.

01:28:27.707 --> 01:28:29.788
Ho-ho-ho!

01:28:31.628 --> 01:28:34.966
Happy Hanukkah and to all, sayonara!

01:28:49.520 --> 01:28:52.859
- You fired him?
- You stay out of this.

01:28:53.900 --> 01:28:58.138
Wally, play some music. This is a party.
Dance, everybody dance.

01:28:58.238 --> 01:29:00.557
- Some high drama here.
- I'll fix it.

01:29:00.657 --> 01:29:04.362
- May I have this dance?
- You can go fuck yourself.

01:29:05.537 --> 01:29:08.481
Come here.
You know where you're going here?

01:29:08.581 --> 01:29:11.568
You wanna give it away
because he wants to live in Russia?

01:29:11.668 --> 01:29:16.239
- What the hell did he do? Sign a petition.
- These guys control the network.

01:29:16.339 --> 01:29:18.950
He's your friend.
Tell 'em to go to hell.

01:29:19.050 --> 01:29:21.578
I'm not committing suicide
for Art or anyone.

01:29:21.678 --> 01:29:25.790
You are so full of shit.
You're worse than they are.

01:29:25.890 --> 01:29:29.794
Who did this? Who did this?
Was it you, Luanna?

01:29:29.894 --> 01:29:33.756
You smug bitch.
Did you put my uncle's name on a list?

01:29:33.856 --> 01:29:39.554
