in the LA Times,

01:34:40.622 --> 01:34:44.776
The whole blacklisting thing
is coming out this Sunday.

01:34:44.876 --> 01:34:47.362
You know what he said?

01:34:47.462 --> 01:34:51.533
"I don't much about Art,
but I know what I like."

01:34:51.633 --> 01:34:55.220
Very clever line.
Did you write it for him?

01:34:58.056 --> 01:35:03.055
15 years, Dixie.
I can't drag it around any more.

01:35:04.270 --> 01:35:07.799
I don't wanna end up
writing for Beat the Clock,

01:35:07.899 --> 01:35:13.596
Art, you're my uncle and I love you.
Do what you gotta do, all right?

01:35:13.696 --> 01:35:17.642
There's a kicker.
The network wants a special.

01:35:17.742 --> 01:35:20.812
Eddie Sparks' 25th anniversary
of the first tour.

01:35:20.912 --> 01:35:25.108
- They're throwing money at him.
- America, the land of the fee.

01:35:25.208 --> 01:35:27.704
Two weeks in Vietnam.

01:35:28.795 --> 01:35:33.592
We got Loretta, Wally,
everybody from the old group.

01:35:34.300 --> 01:35:37.579
- Not everybody.
- At least hear him out.

01:35:37.679 --> 01:35:40.248
Would you do that? For me?

01:35:40.348 --> 01:35:43.960
For old times. We owe him, Dixie.

01:35:44.060 --> 01:35:46.141
I owe him, all right.

01:35:47.272 --> 01:35:49.353
He's outside.

01:35:51.776 --> 01:35:55.763
He was afraid to come in. He's out there
sitting in the goddamn limousine.

01:35:55.863 --> 01:35:58.786
Can I tell him it's OK to come in?

01:36:00.285 --> 01:36:02.562
He sent you in here for this?

01:36:02.662 --> 01:36:05.064
Who's he gonna send?

01:36:05.164 --> 01:36:08.087
Sam's dead. The girls are gone.

01:36:09.210 --> 01:36:11.967
Margaret's left him. We're all he's got.

01:36:15.466 --> 01:36:17.577
Come here.

01:36:17.677 --> 01:36:22.207
- Look, it's Eddie Sparks, right there.
- Oh, yeah. Look, Eddie Sparks.

01:36:22.307 --> 01:36:25.919
- Hi, Mr Sparks. How you doing?
- Hi. I'm looking for Dixie.

01:36:26.019 --> 01:36:30.401
- She's waiting for you right over there.
- Thanks.

01:36:34.777 --> 01:36:36.858
Excuse me, sir.

01:36:39.324 --> 01:36:41.701
It's Eddie Sparks!

01:36:51.127 --> 01:36:53.988
- Mind if I sit down?
- It's a free country.

01:36:54.088 --> 01:36:56.169
So far, anyway.

01:37:05.099 --> 01:37:07.180
So...

01:37:09.854 --> 01:37:12.549
Art, you spoke to him, yeah?

01:37:12.649 --> 01:37:14.611
Oh, yeah.

01:37:16.152 --> 01:37:19.264
- So what do you think?
- I think your hairpiece is too tight.

01:37:19.364 --> 01:37:23.184
It's starting to affect your brain.

01:37:23.284 --> 01:37:25.365
Always with the quips.

01:37:28.498 --> 01:37:30.994
You know, you and me.

01:37:32.502 --> 01:37:34.167
You and me.

01:37:35.588 --> 01:37:39.009
Back together again. We could show 'em.

01:37:41.177 --> 01:37:44.634
Dixie, I wanna do it again.

01:37:46.641 --> 01:37:48.501
Big show, big audience.

01:37:48.601 --> 01:37:52.213
Not this television shit,
300 people in the bedroom.

01:37:52.313 --> 01:37:54.394
I mean 10,000.

01:37:56.150 --> 01:37:58.231
That sound, remember?

01:38:03.533 --> 01:38:05.780
Oh, my.

01:38:11.666 --> 01:38:15.987
I wanna do it again.
What do you say? One more time.

01:38:16.087 --> 01:38:19.115
- I'm not in the business.
- Look...

01:38:19.215 --> 01:38:21.296
We could see Danny.

01:38:22.594 --> 01:38:26.706
Look. He writes to me all the time.
He writes to me all the time.

01:38:26.806 --> 01:38:28.583
Here, look, look.

01:38:28.683 --> 01:38:33.213
Saigon... Now, look...

01:38:33.313 --> 01:38:36.022
Look, Danny. Danny, Danny...

01:38:37.400 --> 01:38:39.481
Look, I got friends.

01:38:40.528 --> 01:38:45.058
State Department, four-star generals,
the president, they owe me.

01:38:45.158 --> 01:38:47.811
Don't do this.

01:38:47.911 --> 01:38:53.233
I could get us in. Don't you wanna
see your boy? Don't you wanna see him?

01:38:53.333 --> 01:38:57.715
I do. Come on. You wanna see him, right?

01:39:00.673 --> 01:39:03.169
You son of a bitch.

01:39:19.567 --> 01:39:23.513
Hey, why is he following the road?

01:39:23.613 --> 01:39:28.852
- Cos he's afraid to fly over the jungle.
- Afraid? Of being seen?

01:39:28.952 --> 01:39:31.033
A lot of VC, right?

01:39:32.163 --> 01:39:35.024
I'll be straight with you, Eddie.
I don't like this.

01:39:35.124 --> 01:39:39.070
You got no business being here.
I can't guarantee your safety.

01:39:39.170 --> 01:39:41.906
Don't worry about it.

01:39:42.006 --> 01:39:45.630
- There it is.
- Where? Over there?

01:39:49.347 --> 01:39:51.428
Oh, my God.

01:40:16.124 --> 01:40:21.503
You got one hour to do what you gotta do
and then we're outta here. Got it?

01:40:46.446 --> 01:40:48.640
Where is he?

01:40:48.740 --> 01:40:51.893
He's out checking perimeter guards.
He'll be back in a while.

01:40:51.993 --> 01:40:56.481
Get your choppers back here by 1430 hours.
I can't guarantee air cover after that.

01:40:56.581 --> 01:40:59.901
Don't worry. We got a big show
in Bien Hoa tonight.

01:41:00.001 --> 01:41:02.082
10,000 guys.

01:41:03.796 --> 01:41:06.672
That's certainly a lot of guys.

01:41:07.926 --> 01:41:12.094
I'd like to get a look
at the stage area if I could.

01:41:14.349 --> 01:41:17.919
I know the men
are gonna really enjoy the show.

01:41:18.019 --> 01:41:20.380
- I hope so.
- Yeah.

01:41:20.480 --> 01:41:22.561
Thank you, Major.

01:41:27.278 --> 01:41:29.359
Pretty exciting, huh?

01:41:30.031 --> 01:41:32.361
Yeah, I guess so.

01:41:37.080 --> 01:41:39.576
Yeah? Help you, son?

01:41:42.794 --> 01:41:46.168
So I finally got you two
in the same room.

01:41:48.841 --> 01:41:50.785
Danny.

01:41:50.885 --> 01:41:54.164
- Danny, Danny, Danny.
- Ma.

01:41:54.264 --> 01:41:57.223
It's OK. It's OK, Ma.

01:42:02.230 --> 01:42:03.350
Hello, son.

01:42:04.440 --> 01:42:07.067
Good to see you again.

01:42:20.582 --> 01:42:24.068
You're mixing it up pretty good,
I hear, huh? Huh?

01:42:24.168 --> 01:42:26.250
Sir?

01:42:29.549 --> 01:42:32.887
Charlie action, firefights, like that.

01:42:35.221 --> 01:42:37.302
Yeah.

01:42:39.434 --> 01:42:41.312
They're out there.

01:42:42.520 --> 01:42:45.089
You look like hell.

01:42:45.189 --> 01:42:48.593
I'm fine. I'm fine, Ma.

01:42:48.693 --> 01:42:54.736
I can't tell you how damn proud we are
of what you're doing here.

01:42:57.076 --> 01:43:00.647
We're gonna beat
those little bastards, you know.

01:43:00.747 --> 01:43:03.525
Yes, sir.

01:43:03.625 --> 01:43:06.121
As soon as we find 'em.

01:43:13.468 --> 01:43:15.964
- Williams.
- Captain Danny.

01:43:17.931 --> 01:43:19.513
- O'Connor.
- Hi, Captain.

01:43:46.543 --> 01:43:48.194
Come on.

01:43:48.294 --> 01:43:50.447
What? What is it, Danny?

01:43:50.547 --> 01:43:53.469
Honey, talk to me, for God's sake.

01:43:54.384 --> 01:43:58.552
It's a shame, really.
Such a beautiful country.

01:44:00.181 --> 01:44:04.978
I don't know how it's ever gonna
come back from all this.

01:44:19.117 --> 01:44:22.020
- He doesn't get it, does he?
- Honey, don't say that.

01:44:22.120 --> 01:44:25.440
He moved heaven and earth
to bring us here.

01:44:25.540 --> 01:44:28.036
With the cameras.

01:44:30.587 --> 01:44:34.240
- He's gonna get it all on film, right?
- Why are you surprised?

01:44:34.340 --> 01:44:37.577
What have you been writing him
all this time?

01:44:37.677 --> 01:44:39.758
What he wanted to hear.

01:44:40.847 --> 01:44:43.936
- What'd you want me to write?
- The truth.

01:44:45.685 --> 01:44:47.766
The truth?

01:44:54.235 --> 01:44:57.158
See that kid up there?

01:44:58.281 --> 01:45:00.029
The corporal?

01:45:01.451 --> 01:45:03.019
Yeah.

01:45:03.119 --> 01:45:05.563
He's a sweet kid.

01:45:05.663 --> 01:45:07.732
He's from Chicago.

01:45:07.832 --> 01:45:10.542
His father's a schoolteacher.

01:45:14.464 --> 01:45:16.960
He collects ears.

01:45:22.513 --> 01:45:25.638
He cuts the ears off of dead bodies.

01:45:27.894 --> 01:45:31.714
He's got a hell
of a little collection of 'em.

01:45:31.814 --> 01:45:33.895
In 20, 25 years...

01:45:37.487 --> 01:45:41.027
he's gonna sell them stateside, he says.

01:45:53.127 --> 01:45:55.208
I gotta send him home.

01:45:57.799 --> 01:46:00.924
He's only 19 years old and he's gone.

01:46:02.720 --> 01:46:04.801
It's a nightmare.

01:46:05.890 --> 01:46:07.971
Please.

01:46:14.065 --> 01:46:20.680
You know, Eddie, he's got a lot of friends.
He could get you out of here.

01:46:20.780 --> 01:46:24.830
I'm a captain, Mom.
I got men under me here.

01:46:28.329 --> 01:46:30.732
And anyway....

01:46:30.832 --> 01:46:33.542
it'd break Eddie's heart.

01:46:36.588 --> 01:46:40.617
I went to the doctor.
He said my sex life was all in my head.

01:46:40.717 --> 01:46:44.245
I said "Yeah, I know,
I want it lowered."

01:46:45.471 --> 01:46:51.669
You gotta laugh or else they're gonna sell me
to the VC for target practice.

01:46:51.769 --> 01:46:54.506
- Where are the girls?
- Girls!

01:46:54.606 --> 01:46:58.443
- Girls!
- Hold it. Did I hear girls?

01:47:01.529 --> 01:47:03.491
We got girls!

01:47:04.908 --> 01:47:08.246
We got girls!

01:47:09.746 --> 01:47:11.856
Hey, Janie, come here!

01:48:34.414 --> 01:48:36.495
Hey, hey, hey!

01:48:38.877 --> 01:48:40.945
Hold it, hold it.

01:48:41.045 --> 01:48:43.624
Hold it, hold it. Guys, guys, guys.

01:48:46.551 --> 01:48:48.453
Come here, come here.

01:48:48.553 --> 01:48:51.206
Let's have a hand
for little Janie Perkins.

01:48:53.933 --> 01:48:58.316
She'll be back later.
She's gonna do more later. Lighten up.

01:48:59.105 --> 01:49:01.683
Now back off here a little bit.

01:49:02.567 --> 01:49:05.489
I got a special treat for you guys.

01:49:06.446 --> 01:49:08.527
I'm gonna tell you now.

01:49:09.490 --> 01:49:13.561
You know your captain Danny Leonard?

01:49:13.661 --> 01:49:15.955
Hell of a man, hell of a man.

01:49:19.000 --> 01:49:20.713
His mother...

01:49:21.711 --> 01:49:27.470
His mother flew 12,000 miles
to be with him and to be with you.

01:49:32.388 --> 01:49:35.750
Best singer I've ever heard.

01:49:35.850 --> 01:49:39.087
She's here for you guys.
Let me bring her out.

01:49:39.187 --> 01:49:42.193
The wonderful Miss Dixie Leonard.

01:49:49.239 --> 01:49:51.735
Dixie! Dixie!

01:49:52.867 --> 01:49:54.948
All right, shut up.

01:49:55.995 --> 01:49:58.076
Shut up!

01:49:59.332 --> 01:50:04.904
You guys are the sorriest bunch of grunts
I ever saw in my life.

01:50:05.004 --> 01:50:07.198
Where the hell did you learn
your manners?

01:50:07.298 --> 01:50:11.828
