"excuse me" before you attack a lady?

01:50:11.928 --> 01:50:14.768
Show us your tits, Mama!

01:50:22.313 --> 01:50:27.111
I would, sonny,
but you'd probably have a heart attack.

01:50:30.196 --> 01:50:33.404
All right, shut the fuck up.

01:50:36.327 --> 01:50:41.125
It's Christmas time.
Gonna sing a little song for you.

01:51:18.661 --> 01:51:22.232
I need stuff like Danny listening.

01:51:22.332 --> 01:51:25.955
He's not in the audience.
I can't find him.

01:51:28.379 --> 01:51:30.792
Keep looking, will you?

01:53:49.979 --> 01:53:51.728
Incoming!

01:53:53.483 --> 01:53:54.592
Drop! Drop!

01:53:54.692 --> 01:53:56.773
Move it! Move it! Move it!

01:53:58.404 --> 01:54:01.944
Get down in there, you hear me?
Don't come out!

01:57:24.319 --> 01:57:29.780
We flew back with him
on the plane, Eddie and me,

01:57:30.575 --> 01:57:33.415
And... we buried him,

01:57:34.204 --> 01:57:36.700
and we never spoke again,

01:57:38.875 --> 01:57:41.335
25 years,

01:57:53.306 --> 01:57:57.178
Listen, why don't you just relax?

01:57:58.394 --> 01:58:02.382
Just close your eyes
for a couple of minutes, OK?

01:58:02.482 --> 01:58:04.563
Do that for me?

01:58:05.985 --> 01:58:08.066
I'll be right back.

01:58:12.825 --> 01:58:18.536
The thing you wanna avoid
is outlasting everybody.

01:58:20.583 --> 01:58:23.319
Can you remember that?

01:58:23.419 --> 01:58:25.500
Sure.

01:58:26.047 --> 01:58:28.128
Good.

01:58:29.676 --> 01:58:31.757
Just close your eyes.

01:58:33.513 --> 01:58:35.594
I've gotta...

01:58:36.182 --> 01:58:40.434
I'm gonna be right back, OK?
Just two minutes, OK?

01:58:50.238 --> 01:58:53.600
Where the hell are you? We go in 20 minutes.
Eddie's asking for her.

01:58:53.700 --> 01:58:58.605
Forget it. You don't want her
on the stage with him. Not on live TV.

01:58:58.705 --> 01:59:01.191
- What happened?
- Her life.

01:59:01.291 --> 01:59:03.985
Jesus, don't get poetic with me,
you little putz!

01:59:04.085 --> 01:59:09.199
- Listen, it won't work, Stan.
- OK, dump her and get your ass down here.

01:59:09.299 --> 01:59:13.882
I don't think so, Stan.
She needs to be with somebody.

01:59:16.639 --> 01:59:18.803
Is everything all right?

01:59:19.893 --> 01:59:22.685
Go see if Joan Collins
is out in the audience.

01:59:25.565 --> 01:59:27.646
Miss Leonard?

01:59:29.903 --> 01:59:35.827
Jesus. Miss Leonard, are you all right?
Miss Leonard! Miss Leonard!

01:59:37.911 --> 01:59:40.438
Miss Leonard.

01:59:40.538 --> 01:59:43.358
Open this door, goddammit! Dixie!

01:59:43.458 --> 01:59:45.539
It opens out, genius.

01:59:50.548 --> 01:59:53.076
You're dressed.

01:59:53.176 --> 01:59:55.423
Balenciaga. What do you think?

01:59:57.972 --> 02:00:00.291
You look beautiful.

02:00:00.391 --> 02:00:03.294
You thought I was taking
a bunch of sleeping pills.

02:00:03.394 --> 02:00:04.212
No, I...

02:00:04.312 --> 02:00:07.173
This dress cost me.
I ain't gonna waste it. Let's go.

02:00:07.273 --> 02:00:09.759
You're gonna do it?

02:00:09.859 --> 02:00:14.264
50 million people.
He can't handle that by himself.

02:00:14.364 --> 02:00:17.475
And that better be a stretch limo
or you're in deep shit.

02:00:17.575 --> 02:00:19.602
Yes, ma'am.

02:00:39.556 --> 02:00:44.057
Stand by with the girls, please.
Ready to cue the girls in and cue 'em in.

02:01:02.120 --> 02:01:06.372
And ready, boys.
And dissolve... Send them in.

02:01:20.346 --> 02:01:23.833
- She's coming!
- Here she is!

02:01:23.933 --> 02:01:27.045
Miss Leonard! Can we have a picture?

02:01:27.145 --> 02:01:29.522
Come on, back off. Back off!

02:01:32.567 --> 02:01:34.636
Let her through!

02:01:34.736 --> 02:01:37.806
Come on, Miss Leonard.

02:01:37.906 --> 02:01:39.987
Please!

02:01:41.075 --> 02:01:43.520
- Keep the hands in.
- What?

02:01:43.620 --> 02:01:48.316
- She's here.
- Great. Get her into make-up quick.

02:01:48.416 --> 02:01:50.627
Standby on two. And take it.

02:01:59.761 --> 02:02:01.329
Get outta the way.

02:02:01.429 --> 02:02:04.415
Miss Leonard, I'm Stan.
I'm the producer.

02:02:04.515 --> 02:02:07.669
This is such an honour.
We're thrilled you decided to come.

02:02:07.769 --> 02:02:10.046
- Where's Eddie?
- No time for that.

02:02:10.146 --> 02:02:14.300
After this number we go to commercial,
then the tape of the president's greeting,

02:02:14.400 --> 02:02:18.805
then the film clips, then we intro
Senator Ramsey for the presentation,

02:02:18.905 --> 02:02:24.352
then you and Eddie, "Glad to be here",
couple of shticks, then you do your thing.

02:02:24.452 --> 02:02:26.938
- Sounds lovely.
- Five minutes,

02:02:27.038 --> 02:02:28.523
- Where?
- Make-up.

02:02:28.623 --> 02:02:30.525
- This way.
- Right over there.

02:02:30.625 --> 02:02:34.378
Where are you going?
Hey, kid, I am talking to you.

02:02:51.646 --> 02:02:55.186
Son of a bitch still makes me nervous.

02:02:56.568 --> 02:03:00.388
You go easy on him.
Remember, he's an endangered species.

02:03:00.488 --> 02:03:02.569
Ain't we all?

02:03:04.409 --> 02:03:07.604
- Thank you.
- For what?

02:03:07.704 --> 02:03:12.484
You know, showing up,
being a pushy assistant.

02:03:12.584 --> 02:03:14.903
Ex pushy assistant.

02:03:15.003 --> 02:03:18.323
You got a bigger talent,
like your mother says.

02:03:18.423 --> 02:03:20.504
You can fix things.

02:03:23.344 --> 02:03:26.469
- Goodbye, Miss Leonard.
- Goodbye.

02:03:27.515 --> 02:03:29.596
Ooh!

02:03:47.493 --> 02:03:51.523
Miss Leonard! I can't believe it.
I'm Lou Presti, Eddie's manager.

02:03:51.623 --> 02:03:55.921
Eddie, look who's here.
You won't believe it.

02:03:59.714 --> 02:04:02.992
Well, the "late" Dixie Leonard.

02:04:03.092 --> 02:04:06.746
- Hello, Eddie.
- Lou, that's five dollars you owe me.

02:04:06.846 --> 02:04:08.957
- You got it.
- We had a little side bet.

02:04:09.057 --> 02:04:13.419
He said "She's not coming. Forget about it.
She can't take the pressure."

02:04:13.519 --> 02:04:16.005
I said "This one, you don't know."

02:04:16.105 --> 02:04:20.009
Couldn't stay away, huh?
50 million people.

02:04:20.109 --> 02:04:22.345
That's a Leica, isn't it?

02:04:22.445 --> 02:04:26.057
Right. That's very good.
Are you a photographer, Miss Leonard?

02:04:26.157 --> 02:04:29.269
No, but my husband was. May I see that?

02:04:29.369 --> 02:04:31.521
Sure, sure.

02:04:31.621 --> 02:04:36.526
- It's kinda heavy. Be careful.
- Yes, I see. Oh, my. Yes.

02:04:36.626 --> 02:04:39.487
Don't touch that.
What the hell are you doin'?

02:04:39.587 --> 02:04:44.325
- Those are all my shots!
- You want pictures of me, you ask me.

02:04:44.425 --> 02:04:46.506
Lou, Lou.

02:04:48.680 --> 02:04:51.624
- Clear the room.
- Please, would you mind, everybody?

02:04:51.724 --> 02:04:55.394
Thank you very much.
Thank you very much.

02:04:56.437 --> 02:04:58.173
Eddie...

02:04:58.273 --> 02:05:00.354
Please, please.

02:05:05.822 --> 02:05:08.892
So I see the years
have not mellowed you.

02:05:08.992 --> 02:05:12.103
You want mellow,
buy yourself a Rudy Vallee record.

02:05:12.203 --> 02:05:14.497
Funny.

02:05:15.957 --> 02:05:19.235
Listen up. You cleared the room.
Now what?

02:05:19.335 --> 02:05:25.241
- I don't know. I thought we could talk.
- I don't wanna talk. I wanna get ready.

02:05:25.341 --> 02:05:27.869
Yeah, but I wanna talk.

02:05:27.969 --> 02:05:30.050
About what?

02:05:32.307 --> 02:05:36.878
How about sleep? Old people
are always talking about sleep.

02:05:36.978 --> 02:05:42.091
- How you been sleeping lately, Eddie?
- Me? Like a baby. How about yourself?

02:05:42.191 --> 02:05:44.273
Not so good.

02:05:45.153 --> 02:05:48.640
I dream a lot. Then I wake up.

02:05:48.740 --> 02:05:53.770
- You should try some warm milk.
- No. I like the dreams.

02:05:53.870 --> 02:05:56.815
They're very enlightening.

02:05:56.915 --> 02:05:59.901
Do you believe
in the unconscious, Eddie?

02:06:00.001 --> 02:06:03.947
Personally, I prefer the conscious.
They pay more attention.

02:06:04.047 --> 02:06:08.284
You still got your touch, Eddie. Even though
you do look like a goddamn turtle.

02:06:08.384 --> 02:06:11.871
- Thank you. You look good yourself.
- Thanks. Mind if I smoke?

02:06:11.971 --> 02:06:15.416
- I don't care if you burn.
- What a prince.

02:06:15.516 --> 02:06:19.754
I had a doosey of a dream last night.
You were in it. You wanna hear it?

02:06:19.854 --> 02:06:21.935
- No.
- It was fantastic.

02:06:24.525 --> 02:06:28.388
I dreamed I died and went to heaven.

02:06:28.488 --> 02:06:33.783
And the angels... the angels told me
I could ask God one question.

02:06:35.078 --> 02:06:40.900
So I said... I was very excited...
I said "God, first you took Michael."

02:06:41.000 --> 02:06:47.257
"I sort of understand that. He was wild.
He was reckless. Fantastic in bed."

02:06:48.258 --> 02:06:50.339
"OK, so Michael."

02:06:51.427 --> 02:06:56.082
"But then Danny too.
Why'd you take 'em both? I gotta know."

02:06:56.182 --> 02:06:58.960
And you know what God said?

02:06:59.060 --> 02:07:03.756
He said "It's the price."
I said "What for?"

02:07:03.856 --> 02:07:09.387
He said "It's the price for the good times,
for the fun, for the laughs,

02:07:09.487 --> 02:07:13.099
for the applause, for the career,
for you and Eddie."

02:07:13.199 --> 02:07:15.268
"Think there's a free lunch, girlie?"

02:07:15.368 --> 02:07:20.231
He talked like he was from the William Morris
office. In fact, that's who I think he is.

02:07:20.331 --> 02:07:23.109
Yeah. So now you're through?

02:07:23.209 --> 02:07:25.290
No.

02:07:26.212 --> 02:07:28.625
We did it.

02:07:29.716 --> 02:07:32.212
We put a uniform on him.

02:07:34.012 --> 02:07:38.082
- Don't do this.
- He loved us and we put him in the ground.

02:07:38.182 --> 02:07:39.250
All right.

02:07:39.350 --> 02:07:43.338
It's 25 years. I can't go on like this.

02:07:43.438 --> 02:07:45.924
I need you. I can't do it alone.

02:07:46.024 --> 02:07:49.010
You listen to me, you crazy bitch!

02:07:49.110 --> 02:07:51.221
I never killed nobody!

02:07:51.321 --> 02:07:55.240
I never started the wars.
I'm not a fucking general!

02:07:57.869 --> 02:08:00.365
I'm a song-and-dance man.

02:08:03.416 --> 02:08:07.529
We went out there and we made 'em forget
for a couple of hours.

02:08:07.629 --> 02:08:11.616
- It's not that simple.
- I'm proud of what we done, Dixie.

02:08:11.716 --> 02:08:18.164
I'm proud of every minute.
I'm proud of every show. It was an honour.

02:08:18.264 --> 02:08:20.792
- A sacred honour.
- Dixie and Eddie, places,

02:08:20.892 --> 02:08:22.973
Dixie...

02:08:24.270 --> 02:08:26.766
I know he died.

02:08:28.191 --> 02:08:31.511
Him and a million others.
Why don't you mourn for them?

02:08:31.611 --> 02:08:33.972
- I do.
- Well, so do I.

02:08:34.072 --> 02:08:38.977
So do I! But you pick yourself up. You don't
waste your life and chew on this thing!

02:08:39.077 --> 02:08:43.064
I didn't waste my life.
I made something of my life.

02:08:43.164 --> 02:08:47.444
I gave birth to him.
I nursed him. I sang him to sleep.

02:08:47.544 --> 02:08:51.677
And they massacred him.
For what? For honour!

02:08:53.591 --> 02:08:56.550
Fuck honour! I want my son back!

02:09:15.405 --> 02:09:17.486
I don't need this.

02:09:22.996 --> 02:09:25.077
I don't need you.

02:09:27.667 --> 02:09:29.903
I don't need anybody.

02:09:30.003 --> 02:09:32.084
Go on, you old fraud.

02:09:33.590 --> 02:09:36.409
Get your medal.

02:09:36.509 --> 02:09:38.970
I hope it was worth it.

02:09:44.559 --> 02:09:48.713
..and, certainly,
none more distinctly American

02:09:48.813 --> 02:09:52.759
than the two people
we honour here tonight.

02:09:52.859 --> 02:09:58.598
On behalf of the president,
it is my great pleasure

02:09:58.698 --> 02:10:04.854
to present the National Medal of the Arts
to Eddie Sparks and Dixie Leonard.

02:10:08.208 --> 02:10:11.569
Where is she?
Anybody have any idea where she is?

02:10:11.669 --> 02:10:15.031
Take one and cover it. We're on one.

02:10:15.131 --> 02:10:17.461
Three, swing round
and get some audience.

02:10:59.659 --> 02:11:00.827
Bravo!

02:11:06.808 --> 02:11:09.814
I should do this well at my funeral!

02:11:14.023 --> 02:11:16.104
Seriously...

02:11:18.528 --> 02:11:20.609
This is a great honour.

02:11:22.407 --> 02:11:25.143
A great, great honour.

02:11:25.243 --> 02:11:28.563
And Dixie, she couldn't be
with us tonight.

02:11:28.663 --> 02:11:31.733
She's a little under the weather.

02:11:31.833 --> 02:11:36.749
But I know she's watching.
So hang in there, honey. We love you.

02:11:41.926 --> 02:11:46.456
We both want you to know
that we share this honour

02:11:46.556 --> 02:11:52.212
with all the young Americans
who laid down their lives

02:11:52.312 --> 02:11:55.899
for the greatest country
in all the world.

02:12:06.117 --> 02:12:08.613
On the beaches of Normandy...

02:12:09.996 --> 02:12:12.077
the Philippines...

02:12:13.458 --> 02:12:15.539
Korea...

02:12:16.169 --> 02:12:18.250
Vietnam...

02:12:29.515 --> 02:12:33.304
Come on. Eddie, what? Let's go.
Stand by with a commercial.

02:12:35.355 --> 02:12:37.436
Vietnam...

02:12:40.360 --> 02:12:42.441
Vietnam...

02:12:46.532 --> 02:12:50.203
A small... A small fire base on...

02:12:56.459 --> 02:12:59.963
Christmas Day, 1969.

02:13:04.300 --> 02:13:06.381
They...

02:13:11.808 --> 02:13:14.933
They just came at us out of the sun.

02:13:21.192 --> 02:13:24.696
And we lost our boy.

02:13:32.120 --> 02:13:34.616
To tell you the truth, I...

02:13:37.000 --> 02:13:39.496
I haven't been sleeping so good,

02:13:42.338 --> 02:13:44.799
Not so good,

02:13:47.343 --> 02:13:51.891
Because I loved him
like he was my own son.

02:13:56.144 --> 02:13:59.767
I loved him very, very much,

02:14:02.901 --> 02:14:04.982
Danny... I...

02:14:24.422 --> 02:14:27.298
Here she is. I need the spots on her.

02:14:43.358 --> 02:14:45.439
Oh, how great!

02:14:53.826 --> 02:14:56.521
Pipe down, pipe down, will you?

02:15:04.546 --> 02:15:06.627
You know, when I...

02:15:07.507 --> 02:15:10.869
When I first met him, he was nothing.

02:15:11.469 --> 02:15:13.246
Doing it single.

02:15:13.346 --> 02:15:15.427
Bad suit.

02:15:16.599 --> 02:15:19.878
Impersonations, song parodies.

02:15:19.978 --> 02:15:22.297
Terrible.

02:15:22.397 --> 02:15:28.136
But I saw some potential there
and I took him under my wing,

02:15:28.236 --> 02:15:31.181
and I taught him the business.

02:15:31.281 --> 02:15:36.363
I taught him the moves,
the songs, the timing.

02:15:37.537 --> 02:15:41.789
I even taught him
how to impersonate a human being.

02:15:49.340 --> 02:15:51.493
Thank you.

02:15:51.593 --> 02:15:53.674
You're very welcome.

02:15:57.807 --> 02:15:59.888
You know...

02:16:01.227 --> 02:16:04.589
for an old broad,
you're still pretty sexy.

02:16:13.197 --> 02:16:15.279
How would you know?

02:16:16.242 --> 02:16:19.367
Well, I think I'm getting excited.

02:16:22.749 --> 02:16:25.459
Let me know when you're sure.

02:16:27.921 --> 02:16:32.575
Hey, Dixie, they gave me
a big suite upstairs.

02:16:32.674 --> 02:16:33.868
- Really?
- Yeah.

02:16:33.968 --> 02:16:36.725
And I got a big king-size bed.

02:16:39.641 --> 02:16:43.128
- You wanna lie down, Eddie?
- Is that an offer?

02:16:43.227 --> 02:16:45.355
It's a recommendation.

02:16:51.318 --> 02:16:56.349
Look at this. I'm 91 years old.
50 years I've been waiting for this chance.

02:16:56.449 --> 02:16:59.769
- Dixie, please let's go upstairs.
- What, to your room?

02:16:59.869 --> 02:17:02.689
- Yeah.
- Ohh!

02:17:02.789 --> 02:17:05.795
- And then we get undressed?
- Yeah.

02:17:06.668 --> 02:17:09.590
- And then we get into bed?
- Yeah.

02:17:10.547 --> 02:17:12.628
And then what?

02:17:23.268 --> 02:17:25.396
Maybe we'd better dance.

02:17:27.272 --> 02:17:30.091
Thank goodness she showed up.
There is a Santa Claus!

02:17:30.191 --> 02:17:32.603
Wonderful. Stand by, music.

02:17:33.653 --> 02:17:36.556
I'm coming, sweetheart. Are you ready?

02:17:36.656 --> 02:17:40.058
- Wait. I gotta find my feet.
- They're there. Trust me.

02:17:40.159 --> 02:17:42.896
- You ready now?
- Don't hurt yourself.

02:17:42.995 --> 02:17:45.356
Don't worry. And five, six...

